A man was arrested on 28 June 2019, in connection with the attempted murder of a homeless man earlier in the year. He was released from custody the same day. JOHANNESBURG - The suspect arrested by Pretoria police for an alleged attack on a homeless man, has been released. He was supposed to appear in the Pretoria Magistrate's Court on Friday morning, but the case was struck off the roll. The man was arrested on Wednesday in connection with the attempted murder of a homeless man earlier this year. The police's Kay Makhubele said they were not able to immediately link him to the Capital Killer case, where five homeless men have been murdered. 